def load_layouts():
    dfs = []
    for feba_n,lt in LAYOUTS.items():
        df = pd.read_csv(lt['filename'], sep='\t')
        df['feba_n'] = pd.Series([feba_n]*df.shape[0])        
        lt['df']  = df
        dfs.append(df)
    return pd.concat(dfs)

def build_barcode_2_index(feba_n):
    fscore_base_df = pd.read_csv(DATA_DIR + ('gscore/%s/fscore_base.tsv' %feba_n),sep='\t')
    barcode2Index = {}
    for i in range(fscore_base_df.shape[0]):
        fs = fscore_base_df.iloc[i]
        barcode2Index[fs.barcode] = i
        
    return barcode2Index

def build_condition_gene_matrix(barcode2Index, feba_n):
    gscore_base_df = pd.read_csv(DATA_DIR + ('gscore/%s/gscore_base.tsv'%feba_n),sep='\t')
    matrix = np.zeros(shape=(len(barcode2Index),gscore_base_df.shape[0]))    
    for gIndex in range(gscore_base_df.shape[0]):
        gene = gscore_base_df.iloc[gIndex]
        for barcode in str(gene.barcodes).split(','):
            fIndex = barcode2Index.get(barcode)
            if fIndex:
                matrix[fIndex,gIndex] = 1
    return matrix

def build_fscores(barcode2Index, feba_n, itnum):
    fscores = np.zeros(shape=(len(barcode2Index)))    
    fscores_df = pd.read_csv(DATA_DIR + ('gscore/%s/%s.fscore.tsv'%(feba_n,itnum)), sep='\t')
    for i in range(fscores_df.shape[0]):
        fr = fscores_df.iloc[i]
        fIndex = barcode2Index.get(fr.barcode)
        if fIndex:
           fscores[fIndex] = fr.score
    return fscores


def do_lasso_cross_validation(matrix, fscore, cv=3):
    # convert matrix to the sparse version
    A = sparse.coo_matrix(matrix)
    y = fscores
    
    # run lasso cv
    lassocv = LassoCV( cv=cv, fit_intercept=False)
    lassocv.fit(A, y)
    
    res_alpha = lassocv.alpha_
    res_r_alpha = lassocv.alpha_*len(y)*2
    print('Optimal params: r_alpha=%.1f; alpha=%s' %(res_r_alpha, res_alpha))
    
    
    fig = plt.figure()
    ax = fig.add_subplot(1, 1, 1)
    ax.set_xscale('log')
    ax.plot(lassocv.alphas_,lassocv.mse_path_)
    plt.xlabel('alpha')
    plt.ylabel('MSE')
    plt.show()  
    return lassocv
    
    
def do_ridge_cross_validation(matrix, fscore, cv=3):
    # convert matrix to the sparse version

    y = fscores

    ridgecv.fit(A, y)
    
    res_alpha = ridgecv.alpha_
    print('Optimal params: alpha=%s' %(res_alpha))

def do_enet_cross_validation(matrix, fscores, cv=3):
    # convert matrix to the sparse version
    A = sparse.coo_matrix(matrix)
    y = fscores

    # li_ratios to test
    l1_ratios = [.1, .3, .5, .7, .9, .95, .99, 1]

    # run elastic net cv
    enetcv = ElasticNetCV( l1_ratio=l1_ratios,  cv=cv, fit_intercept=False)
    enetcv.fit(A, y)


    res_alpha = enetcv.alpha_
    res_r_alpha = enetcv.alpha_*len(y)*2
    res_l1_ratio = enetcv.l1_ratio_
    
    print('Optimal params: r_alpha=%.1f; l1_ratio=%s; alpha=%s' %(res_r_alpha, res_l1_ratio, res_alpha))
    fig = plt.figure()
    ax = fig.add_subplot(1, 1, 1)
    ax.set_xscale('log')

    for ri, r in enumerate(l1_ratios):
        xx = enetcv.alphas_[ri]
        yy = np.average(enetcv.mse_path_[ri], axis=1)
        ax.plot(xx,yy, label='l1_ratio=%s'%r)
    ax.legend()    
    plt.xlabel('alpha')
    plt.ylabel('MSE')
    plt.show()  
            
        
def plot_compare_fscores(fscores, pred_fscores):
    plt.plot(fscores, pred_fscores, 'o', color = '#1F1FAF1F')
    
    minv = min( min( fscores ), min(pred_fscores)) -1
    maxv = max( max( fscores ), max(pred_fscores)) + 1
    
    plt.plot([minv,maxv],[minv,maxv], color='r')
    
    plt.title('Compare predicted and true fscores')
    plt.xlabel('True fscores')
    plt.ylabel('Predicted fscores')
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.show()    
    
def plot_compare_gscores(gscores, gscore_type, mean_gscores):
    plt.plot(mean_gscores, gscores, 'o', color = '#1F1FAF1F')
    
    minv = min( min( mean_gscores ), min(gscores)) -1
    maxv = max( max( mean_gscores ), max(gscores)) + 1
    
    plt.plot([minv,maxv],[minv,maxv], color='r')
    
    plt.title('Compare mean and %s gscores' % gscore_type)
    plt.xlabel('Mean gscore')
    plt.ylabel('%s gscore' % gscore_type)
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.show()
    
    
def plot_nnls_regression(matrix, feba_n, itnum, show_fscores=False, show_gscores=True):
    fscores_df = pd.read_csv(DATA_DIR + ('gscore/%s/%s.fscore.tsv' %(feba_n,itnum)),sep='\t')    
    gscores_df = pd.read_csv(DATA_DIR + ('gscore/%s/%s.gscore.tsv' %(feba_n,itnum)),sep='\t')    
    
    fscores = fscores_df.score.values
    gscores = gscores_df.score_cnnls.values
    mean_scores = gscores_df.score_mean.values
    
    # compare fscores (true and predicted)
    if show_fscores:
        pred_fscores = np.dot(matrix, gscores)
        plot_compare_fscores(fscores, pred_fscores)

    # Compare gscores (elastic net vs mean score)
    if show_gscores:
        plot_compare_gscores(gscores, 'C-NNLS', mean_scores)    
    
    
def do_lasso_regression(matrix, fscores, r_alpha=1, show_fscores=False, show_gscores=True):
    # convert matrix to the sparse version
    A = sparse.coo_matrix(matrix)
    y = fscores
   
    # run elastic net cv
    lasso = Lasso( alpha=r_alpha/2/len(y), fit_intercept=False)
    lasso.fit(A, y)

    # compare fscores (true and predicted)
    if show_fscores:
        pred_fscores = lasso.predict(A)
        plot_compare_fscores(fscores, pred_fscores)
    
    
    # Compare gscores (elastic net vs mean score)
    if show_gscores:
        mean_scores = np.dot( fscores, matrix )/(0.00000001 + np.sum(matrix, axis=0)  )
        plot_compare_gscores(lasso.coef_, 'Lasso', mean_scores)
    
    return lasso

def filter_mm_ff(mm, ff, min_fscore, min_gcount, min_fcount):
    # Filter by min fscore: only genes with at least one fragment that has fscore > min_fscore
    # are excepted
    if min_fscore is not None:
        print('\tdo min fscore')
        mg = (mm.T * ff).T.max(axis=0)
        gi = np.nonzero( mg > min_fscore )[0]
        fi = np.nonzero( mm[:,gi].sum(axis = 1) > 0 )[0]

        mm = mm[:,gi][fi,:]
        ff = ff[fi]

    # Filter by min numnber of overlapped fragments: only genes that has more than 'min_fcount' 
    # overlapped fragments are excepted
    if min_fcount is not None:
        print('\tdo min fcount')
        gi = np.nonzero( mm.T.sum(axis=1) > min_fcount )[0]
        fi = np.nonzero( mm[:,gi].sum(axis = 1) > 0 )[0]
        mm = mm[:,gi][fi,:]
        ff = ff[fi]

    # Filter by total numnber of genes after all filters are applied
    if min_gcount is not None and len(gi) <= min_gcount: 
        print('\tdo min gcount')                
        mm = None
        ff = None
    
    return (mm,ff)
    
def do_enet_set_cv(feba_ns, min_fscore=None, min_gcount=None, min_fcount=None, l1_ratio=[.1, .3, .5, .7, .9, .95, .99, 1]):
    gcount = []
    fcount = []
    itnums = []
    alphas = []
    l1_ratios = []
    r_alphas = []
    score_r2s = []
        
    itnum_index = 0
    for feba_n in feba_ns:
        d = LAYOUTS_DF[LAYOUTS_DF['feba_n'] == feba_n]
        d = d[d['type'] != 'Time0']

        barcode2index = build_barcode_2_index(feba_n)
        fg_matrix = build_condition_gene_matrix(barcode2index, feba_n)

        for itnum in d.itnum:          
            if TEST_MODE and itnum_index > 3: break
            print('Doing [%s] %s: %s' % (itnum_index, feba_n,itnum) )
            
            mm = fg_matrix
            ff = build_fscores(barcode2index, feba_n, itnum)

            (mm,ff) = filter_mm_ff(mm, ff, min_fscore, min_gcount, min_fcount)
            if mm is None:
                continue
            
            print('\tdo cv')                            
            A = sparse.coo_matrix( mm )
            y = ff
            enetcv = ElasticNetCV( l1_ratio=l1_ratio,  fit_intercept=False, cv=3)
            enetcv.fit(A, y)            

            gcount.append(A.shape[1])
            fcount.append(A.shape[0])    
            itnums.append(feba_n + ':' + itnum)
            alphas.append(enetcv.alpha_)
            l1_ratios.append(enetcv.l1_ratio_)        
            r_alphas.append( enetcv.alpha_*len(y)*2 )
            score_r2s.append( enetcv.score(A,y) )
            itnum_index += 1
    
    df = pd.DataFrame()
    
    df['score_r2'] = score_r2s
    df['gcount'] = gcount
    df['fcount'] = fcount
    df['itnum'] = itnums
    df['alpha'] = alphas
    df['r_alpha'] = r_alphas
    df['l1_ratio'] = l1_ratios
    print('Done!')
    
    return df

def do_enet_combined(feba_ns, min_fscore=None, min_gcount=None, min_fcount=None, l1_ratio=[.1, .3, .5, .7, .9, .95, .99, 1]):
    m_elems = []
    m_row_indices = []
    m_col_indices = []
    f_values = []

    g_offset = 0
    f_offset = 0
    itnums_count = 0


    for feba_n in feba_ns:
        d = LAYOUTS_DF[LAYOUTS_DF['feba_n'] == feba_n]
        d = d[d['type'] != 'Time0']

        barcode2index = build_barcode_2_index(feba_n)
        fg_matrix = build_condition_gene_matrix(barcode2index, feba_n)

        for itnum in d.itnum:
            if TEST_MODE and itnums_count > 3: break
            print('Doing[%s] %s: %s' % (itnums_count, feba_n,itnum) )
            
            mm = fg_matrix
            ff = build_fscores(barcode2index, feba_n, itnum)

            (mm,ff) = filter_mm_ff(mm, ff, min_fscore, min_gcount, min_fcount)
            if  mm is None:
                continue
            

            for i, fscore in enumerate(ff):
                for j in np.nonzero( mm[i] )[0]:
                    m_row_indices.append(i + f_offset) 
                    m_col_indices.append(j + g_offset)
                    m_elems.append(1)                
                f_values.append(fscore)

            f_offset += mm.shape[0]
            g_offset += mm.shape[1]
            itnums_count += 1
            print('\tf_offset=%s; g_offset=%s; m_elems=%s' %(f_offset, g_offset, len(m_elems)) )

    print('Converting sparse matrix..')
    A = sparse.coo_matrix( (m_elems, (m_row_indices, m_col_indices)) )
    y = f_values

    print( 'matrix shape=%s; fvalues=%s' %(A.shape, len(y)) )


    print ('Doing corss validation...')
    enetcv = ElasticNetCV( l1_ratio=l1_ratio,  fit_intercept=False, cv=3)
    enetcv.fit(A, y)
    
    df = pd.DataFrame()
    df['alpha'] = [enetcv.alpha_]
    df['l1_ratio'] = [enetcv.l1_ratio_]
    df['r_alpha'] = [enetcv.alpha_*len(y)*2]
    df['score_r2'] = [enetcv.score(A, y)]
    df['fcount'] = [A.shape[0]]
    df['gcount'] = [A.shape[1]]
    
    print('Done!')
    return df

Elastic Net¶

The objective function:

1 / (2 * n_samples) * ||y - Xw||^2_2 + alpha * l1_ratio * ||w||_1 + 0.5 * alpha * (1 - l1_ratio) * ||w||^2_2

  • l1_ratio = 1 => Lasso
  • l1_ratio = 0 => Ridge

alpha is a parameter that defines the shrinkage, but, the way it is defined, its effect also depeneds on the n_samples.

Let us define r_alpha = 2 * n_smaples * alpha, that do not depened on the number of samples

Conclusion¶

It seems that the shrinkage is too strong.. Look at the max gscore (it is rcnA gene): we know that it should be around 8 (based on both mean score and nnls), but elastic net with "optimal" parameters gives us 5.96.

Why?¶

Possible reasons:

  1. Most of the fscores are around zero, and thus ElasticNetCV optimizes parameters the way to treat well these most abundant "close to zero" values, and thus srhinks too hard... but the most interesting scores are > 2..

  2. Our matrix is very sparse. When we do 3-fold cross validation, we remove 1/3 of samples (fragments, fscores), and try to predict features (gene scores). But becuase of sparcity, it might happen that after removing these samples and because of saprsity, genes will not have even a single covering fragment. In this case the predicted score will be zero, and it may introduce some bias.

Too strong shrinkage: Solution 1¶

Do corss validation ONLY for thouse genes that have at least one covering framgent with fscore > 2

fig = plt.figure( figsize=(15, 12) )
ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')
x_data = enetSetCV_mfs2.r_alpha
y_data = enetSetCV_mfs2.l1_ratio
z_data = enetSetCV_mfs2.score_r2
ax.bar3d( 
        x_data,
        y_data,
        np.zeros(len(z_data)),
        max(x_data)/7/5,
        max(y_data)/7/15,
        z_data
        )
ax.set_xlabel('r_alpha')
ax.set_ylabel('l1_ratio')
ax.set_zlabel('R^2')
plt.title('3-fold cross validation: %s conditions' %len(enetSetCV_mfs2.itnum) )
plt.show()

Lasso¶

The objective function:

(1 / (2 * n_samples)) * ||y - Xw||^2_2 + alpha * ||w||_1

alpha is a parameter that defines the shrinkage, but, the way it is defined, its effect also depeneds on the n_samples.

Let us define r_alpha = 2 * n_smaples * alpha, that do not depened on the number of samples

In [36]:
feba_n = 'FEBA_133'
barcode2index = build_barcode_2_index(feba_n)
fscores = build_fscores(barcode2index, feba_n, 'IT001')
